<Link id="l00145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="145"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Analyze the branching code at the end of MBB, returning</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="146"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// true if it cannot be understood (e.g. it&#39;s a switch dispatch or isn&#39;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="147"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// implemented for a target).  Upon success, this returns false and returns</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="148"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// with the following information in various cases:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="149"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 1 If this block ends with no branches (it just falls through to its succ)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="151"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    just return false, leaving TBB/FBB null.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="152"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 2 If this block ends with only an unconditional branch, it sets TBB to be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="153"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    the destination block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 3 If this block ends with a conditional branch and it falls through to a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    successor block, it sets TBB to be the branch destination block and a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    list of operands that evaluate the condition. These operands can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    passed to other TargetInstrInfo methods to create new branches.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 4 If this block ends with a conditional branch followed by an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    unconditional branch, it returns the &#39;true&#39; destination in TBB, the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    &#39;false&#39; destination in FBB, and a list of operands that evaluate the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    condition.  These operands can be passed to other TargetInstrInfo</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    methods to create new branches.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Note that RemoveBranch and insertBranch must be implemented to support</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// cases where this method returns success.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// If AllowModify is true, then this routine is allowed to modify the basic</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// block (e.g. delete instructions after the unconditional branch).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"></CodeLine>
